64/**
65 * SECTION:hb-subset
66 * @title: hb-subset
67 * @short_description: Subsets font files.
68 * @include: hb-subset.h
69 *
70 * Subsetting reduces the codepoint coverage of font files and removes all data
71 * that is no longer needed. A subset input describes the desired subset. The input is
72 * provided along with a font to the subsetting operation. Output is a new font file
73 * containing only the data specified in the input.
74 *
75 * Currently most outline and bitmap tables are supported: glyf, CFF, CFF2, sbix,
76 * COLR, and CBDT/CBLC. This also includes fonts with variable outlines via OpenType
77 * variations. Notably EBDT/EBLC and SVG are not supported. Layout subsetting is supported
78 * only for OpenType Layout tables (GSUB, GPOS, GDEF). Notably subsetting of graphite or AAT tables
79 * is not yet supported.
80 *
81 * Fonts with graphite or AAT tables may still be subsetted but will likely need to use the
82 * retain glyph ids option and configure the subset to pass through the layout tables untouched.
83 */
84

146static bool _table_is_empty (const hb_face_t *face, hb_tag_t tag)
147{
148 hb_blob_t* blob = hb_face_reference_table (face, tag);
149 bool result = (blob == hb_blob_get_empty ());
150 hb_blob_destroy (blob);
151 return result;
152}
153
154static unsigned int
155_get_table_tags (const hb_subset_plan_t* plan,
156 unsigned int start_offset,
157 unsigned int *table_count, /* IN/OUT */
158 hb_tag_t *table_tags /* OUT */)
159{
160 unsigned num_tables = hb_face_get_table_tags (face: plan->source, start_offset: 0, table_count: nullptr, table_tags: nullptr);
161 if (num_tables)
162 return hb_face_get_table_tags (face: plan->source, start_offset, table_count, table_tags);
163
164 // If face has 0 tables associated with it, assume that it was built from
165 // hb_face_create_tables and thus is unable to list its tables. Fallback to
166 // checking each table type we can handle for existence instead.
167 auto it =
168 hb_concat (
169 + hb_array (array_&: known_tables)
170 | hb_filter ([&] (hb_tag_t tag) {
171 return !_table_is_empty (face: plan->source, tag) && !plan->no_subset_tables.has (k: tag);
172 })
173 | hb_map ([] (hb_tag_t tag) -> hb_tag_t { return tag; }),
174
175 plan->no_subset_tables.iter ()
176 | hb_filter([&] (hb_tag_t tag) {
177 return !_table_is_empty (face: plan->source, tag);
178 }));
179
180 it += start_offset;
181
182 unsigned num_written = 0;
183 while (bool (it) && num_written < *table_count)
184 table_tags[num_written++] = *it++;
185
186 *table_count = num_written;
187 return num_written;
188}

191static unsigned
192_plan_estimate_subset_table_size (hb_subset_plan_t *plan,
193 unsigned table_len,
194 bool same_size)
195{
196 unsigned src_glyphs = plan->source->get_num_glyphs ();
197 unsigned dst_glyphs = plan->glyphset ()->get_population ();
198
199 if (unlikely (!src_glyphs) || same_size)
200 return 512 + table_len;
201
202 return 512 + (unsigned) (table_len * sqrt (x: (double) dst_glyphs / src_glyphs));
203}

205/*
206 * Repack the serialization buffer if any offset overflows exist.
207 */
208static hb_blob_t*
209_repack (hb_tag_t tag, const hb_serialize_context_t& c)
210{
211 if (!c.offset_overflow ())
212 return c.copy_blob ();
213
214 hb_blob_t* result = hb_resolve_overflows (packed: c.object_graph (), table_tag: tag);
215
216 if (unlikely (!result))
217 {
218 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c offset overflow resolution failed.",
219 HB_UNTAG (tag));
220 return nullptr;
221 }
222
223 return result;
224}
225
226template<typename TableType>
227static
228bool
229_try_subset (const TableType *table,
230 hb_vector_t<char>* buf,
231 hb_subset_context_t* c /* OUT */)
232{
233 c->serializer->start_serialize<TableType> ();
234 if (c->serializer->in_error ()) return false;
235
236 bool needed = table->subset (c);
237 if (!c->serializer->ran_out_of_room ())
238 {
239 c->serializer->end_serialize ();
240 return needed;
241 }
242
243 unsigned buf_size = buf->allocated;
244 buf_size = buf_size * 2 + 16;
245
246
247
248
249 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c ran out of room; reallocating to %u bytes.",
250 HB_UNTAG (c->table_tag), buf_size);
251
252 if (unlikely (buf_size > c->source_blob->length * 16 ||
253 !buf->alloc (buf_size, true)))
254 {
255 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c failed to reallocate %u bytes.",
256 HB_UNTAG (c->table_tag), buf_size);
257 return needed;
258 }
259
260 c->serializer->reset (start_: buf->arrayZ, size: buf->allocated);
261 return _try_subset (table, buf, c);
262}
263
264template<typename TableType>
265static bool
266_subset (hb_subset_plan_t *plan, hb_vector_t<char> &buf)
267{
268 hb_blob_ptr_t<TableType> source_blob = plan->source_table<TableType> ();
269 const TableType *table = source_blob.get ();
270
271 hb_tag_t tag = TableType::tableTag;
272 if (!source_blob.get_blob()->data)
273 {
274 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr,
275 "OT::%c%c%c%c::subset sanitize failed on source table.", HB_UNTAG (tag));
276 source_blob.destroy ();
277 return false;
278 }
279
280 /* Tables that we want to allocate same space as the source table. For GSUB/GPOS it's
281 * because those are expensive to subset, so giving them more room is fine. */
282 bool same_size_table = TableType::tableTag == HB_OT_TAG_GSUB ||
283 TableType::tableTag == HB_OT_TAG_GPOS ||
284 TableType::tableTag == HB_OT_TAG_name;
285
286 unsigned buf_size = _plan_estimate_subset_table_size (plan, source_blob.get_length (), same_size_table);
287 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr,
288 "OT::%c%c%c%c initial estimated table size: %u bytes.", HB_UNTAG (tag), buf_size);
289 if (unlikely (!buf.alloc (buf_size)))
290 {
291 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c failed to allocate %u bytes.", HB_UNTAG (tag), buf_size);
292 source_blob.destroy ();
293 return false;
294 }
295
296 bool needed = false;
297 hb_serialize_context_t serializer (buf.arrayZ, buf.allocated);
298 {
299 hb_subset_context_t c (source_blob.get_blob (), plan, &serializer, tag);
300 needed = _try_subset (table, &buf, &c);
301 }
302 source_blob.destroy ();
303
304 if (serializer.in_error () && !serializer.only_offset_overflow ())
305 {
306 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c::subset FAILED!", HB_UNTAG (tag));
307 return false;
308 }
309
310 if (!needed)
311 {
312 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c::subset table subsetted to empty.", HB_UNTAG (tag));
313 return true;
314 }
315
316 bool result = false;
317 hb_blob_t *dest_blob = _repack (tag, c: serializer);
318 if (dest_blob)
319 {
320 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr,
321 "OT::%c%c%c%c final subset table size: %u bytes.",
322 HB_UNTAG (tag), dest_blob->length);
323 result = plan->add_table (tag, contents: dest_blob);
324 hb_blob_destroy (blob: dest_blob);
325 }
326
327 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "OT::%c%c%c%c::subset %s",
328 HB_UNTAG (tag), result ? "success" : "FAILED!");
329 return result;
330}
331
332static bool
333_is_table_present (hb_face_t *source, hb_tag_t tag)
334{
335
336 if (!hb_face_get_table_tags (face: source, start_offset: 0, table_count: nullptr, table_tags: nullptr)) {
337 // If face has 0 tables associated with it, assume that it was built from
338 // hb_face_create_tables and thus is unable to list its tables. Fallback to
339 // checking if the blob associated with tag is empty.
340 return !_table_is_empty (face: source, tag);
341 }
342
343 hb_tag_t table_tags[32];
344 unsigned offset = 0, num_tables = ARRAY_LENGTH (table_tags);
345 while (((void) hb_face_get_table_tags (face: source, start_offset: offset, table_count: &num_tables, table_tags), num_tables))
346 {
347 for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_tables; ++i)
348 if (table_tags[i] == tag)
349 return true;
350 offset += num_tables;
351 }
352 return false;
353}
354
355static bool
356_should_drop_table (hb_subset_plan_t *plan, hb_tag_t tag)
357{
358 if (plan->drop_tables.has (k: tag))
359 return true;
360
361 switch (tag)
362 {
363 case HB_TAG ('c','v','a','r'): /* hint table, fallthrough */
364 return plan->all_axes_pinned || (plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING);
365
366 case HB_TAG ('c','v','t',' '): /* hint table, fallthrough */
367 case HB_TAG ('f','p','g','m'): /* hint table, fallthrough */
368 case HB_TAG ('p','r','e','p'): /* hint table, fallthrough */
369 case HB_TAG ('h','d','m','x'): /* hint table, fallthrough */
370 case HB_TAG ('V','D','M','X'): /* hint table, fallthrough */
371 return plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING;
372
373#ifdef HB_NO_SUBSET_LAYOUT
374 // Drop Layout Tables if requested.
375 case HB_OT_TAG_GDEF:
376 case HB_OT_TAG_GPOS:
377 case HB_OT_TAG_GSUB:
378 case HB_TAG ('m','o','r','x'):
379 case HB_TAG ('m','o','r','t'):
380 case HB_TAG ('k','e','r','x'):
381 case HB_TAG ('k','e','r','n'):
382 return true;
383#endif
384
385 case HB_TAG ('a','v','a','r'):
386 case HB_TAG ('f','v','a','r'):
387 case HB_TAG ('g','v','a','r'):
388 case HB_OT_TAG_HVAR:
389 case HB_OT_TAG_VVAR:
390 case HB_TAG ('M','V','A','R'):
391 return plan->all_axes_pinned;
392
393 default:
394 return false;
395 }
396}
397
398static bool
399_passthrough (hb_subset_plan_t *plan, hb_tag_t tag)
400{
401 hb_blob_t *source_table = hb_face_reference_table (face: plan->source, tag);
402 bool result = plan->add_table (tag, contents: source_table);
403 hb_blob_destroy (blob: source_table);
404 return result;
405}
406
407static bool
408_dependencies_satisfied (hb_subset_plan_t *plan, hb_tag_t tag,
409 const hb_set_t &subsetted_tags,
410 const hb_set_t &pending_subset_tags)
411{
412 switch (tag)
413 {
414 case HB_OT_TAG_hmtx:
415 case HB_OT_TAG_vmtx:
416 case HB_OT_TAG_maxp:
417 return !plan->normalized_coords || !pending_subset_tags.has (HB_OT_TAG_glyf);
418 default:
419 return true;
420 }
421}
422
423static bool
424_subset_table (hb_subset_plan_t *plan,
425 hb_vector_t<char> &buf,
426 hb_tag_t tag)
427{
428 if (plan->no_subset_tables.has (k: tag)) {
429 return _passthrough (plan, tag);
430 }
431
432 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "subset %c%c%c%c", HB_UNTAG (tag));
433 switch (tag)
434 {
435 case HB_OT_TAG_glyf: return _subset<const OT::glyf> (plan, buf);
436 case HB_OT_TAG_hdmx: return _subset<const OT::hdmx> (plan, buf);
437 case HB_OT_TAG_name: return _subset<const OT::name> (plan, buf);
438 case HB_OT_TAG_head:
439 if (_is_table_present (source: plan->source, HB_OT_TAG_glyf) && !_should_drop_table (plan, HB_OT_TAG_glyf))
440 return true; /* skip head, handled by glyf */
441 return _subset<const OT::head> (plan, buf);
442 case HB_OT_TAG_hhea: return true; /* skip hhea, handled by hmtx */
443 case HB_OT_TAG_hmtx: return _subset<const OT::hmtx> (plan, buf);
444 case HB_OT_TAG_vhea: return true; /* skip vhea, handled by vmtx */
445 case HB_OT_TAG_vmtx: return _subset<const OT::vmtx> (plan, buf);
446 case HB_OT_TAG_maxp: return _subset<const OT::maxp> (plan, buf);
447 case HB_OT_TAG_sbix: return _subset<const OT::sbix> (plan, buf);
448 case HB_OT_TAG_loca: return true; /* skip loca, handled by glyf */
449 case HB_OT_TAG_cmap: return _subset<const OT::cmap> (plan, buf);
450 case HB_OT_TAG_OS2 : return _subset<const OT::OS2 > (plan, buf);
451 case HB_OT_TAG_post: return _subset<const OT::post> (plan, buf);
452 case HB_OT_TAG_COLR: return _subset<const OT::COLR> (plan, buf);
453 case HB_OT_TAG_CPAL: return _subset<const OT::CPAL> (plan, buf);
454 case HB_OT_TAG_CBLC: return _subset<const OT::CBLC> (plan, buf);
455 case HB_OT_TAG_CBDT: return true; /* skip CBDT, handled by CBLC */
456 case HB_OT_TAG_MATH: return _subset<const OT::MATH> (plan, buf);
457
458#ifndef HB_NO_SUBSET_CFF
459 case HB_OT_TAG_cff1: return _subset<const OT::cff1> (plan, buf);
460 case HB_OT_TAG_cff2: return _subset<const OT::cff2> (plan, buf);
461 case HB_OT_TAG_VORG: return _subset<const OT::VORG> (plan, buf);
462#endif
463
464#ifndef HB_NO_SUBSET_LAYOUT
465 case HB_OT_TAG_GDEF: return _subset<const OT::GDEF> (plan, buf);
466 case HB_OT_TAG_GSUB: return _subset<const GSUB> (plan, buf);
467 case HB_OT_TAG_GPOS: return _subset<const GPOS> (plan, buf);
468 case HB_OT_TAG_gvar: return _subset<const OT::gvar> (plan, buf);
469 case HB_OT_TAG_HVAR: return _subset<const OT::HVAR> (plan, buf);
470 case HB_OT_TAG_VVAR: return _subset<const OT::VVAR> (plan, buf);
471#endif
472 case HB_OT_TAG_fvar:
473 if (plan->user_axes_location.is_empty ()) return _passthrough (plan, tag);
474 return _subset<const OT::fvar> (plan, buf);
475 case HB_OT_TAG_STAT:
476 /*TODO(qxliu): change the condition as we support more complex
477 * instancing operation*/
478 if (plan->all_axes_pinned) return _subset<const OT::STAT> (plan, buf);
479 else return _passthrough (plan, tag);
480
481 default:
482 if (plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_PASSTHROUGH_UNRECOGNIZED)
483 return _passthrough (plan, tag);
484
485 // Drop table
486 return true;
487 }
488}
489
490static void _attach_accelerator_data (hb_subset_plan_t* plan,
491 hb_face_t* face /* IN/OUT */)
492{
493 if (!plan->inprogress_accelerator) return;
494
495 // Transfer the accelerator from the plan to us.
496 hb_subset_accelerator_t* accel = plan->inprogress_accelerator;
497 plan->inprogress_accelerator = nullptr;
498
499 if (accel->in_error ())
500 {
501 hb_subset_accelerator_t::destroy (p: accel);
502 return;
503 }
504
505 // Populate caches that need access to the final tables.
506 hb_blob_ptr_t<OT::cmap> cmap_ptr (hb_sanitize_context_t ().reference_table<OT::cmap> (face));
507 accel->cmap_cache = OT::cmap::create_filled_cache (source_table: cmap_ptr);
508 accel->destroy_cmap_cache = OT::SubtableUnicodesCache::destroy;
509
510 if (!hb_face_set_user_data(face,
511 key: hb_subset_accelerator_t::user_data_key(),
512 data: accel,
513 destroy: hb_subset_accelerator_t::destroy,
514 replace: true))
515 hb_subset_accelerator_t::destroy (p: accel);
516}
517
518/**
519 * hb_subset_or_fail:
520 * @source: font face data to be subset.
521 * @input: input to use for the subsetting.
522 *
523 * Subsets a font according to provided input. Returns nullptr
524 * if the subset operation fails.
525 *
526 * Since: 2.9.0
527 **/
528hb_face_t *
529hb_subset_or_fail (hb_face_t *source, const hb_subset_input_t *input)
530{
531 if (unlikely (!input || !source)) return hb_face_get_empty ();
532
533 hb_subset_plan_t *plan = hb_subset_plan_create_or_fail (face: source, input);
534 if (unlikely (!plan)) {
535 return nullptr;
536 }
537
538 hb_face_t * result = hb_subset_plan_execute_or_fail (plan);
539 hb_subset_plan_destroy (plan);
540 return result;
541}
542
543
544/**
545 * hb_subset_plan_execute_or_fail:
546 * @plan: a subsetting plan.
547 *
548 * Executes the provided subsetting @plan.
549 *
550 * Return value:
551 * on success returns a reference to generated font subset. If the subsetting operation fails
552 * returns nullptr.
553 *
554 * Since: 4.0.0
555 **/
556hb_face_t *
557hb_subset_plan_execute_or_fail (hb_subset_plan_t *plan)
558{
559 if (unlikely (!plan || plan->in_error ())) {
560 return nullptr;
561 }
562
563 hb_tag_t table_tags[32];
564 unsigned offset = 0, num_tables = ARRAY_LENGTH (table_tags);
565
566 hb_set_t subsetted_tags, pending_subset_tags;
567 while (((void) _get_table_tags (plan, start_offset: offset, table_count: &num_tables, table_tags), num_tables))
568 {
569 for (unsigned i = 0; i < num_tables; ++i)
570 {
571 hb_tag_t tag = table_tags[i];
572 if (_should_drop_table (plan, tag)) continue;
573 pending_subset_tags.add (g: tag);
574 }
575
576 offset += num_tables;
577 }
578
579 hb_vector_t<char> buf;
580 buf.alloc (size: 4096 - 16);
581
582
583 bool success = true;
584
585 while (!pending_subset_tags.is_empty ())
586 {
587 if (subsetted_tags.in_error ()
588 || pending_subset_tags.in_error ()) {
589 success = false;
590 goto end;
591 }
592
593 bool made_changes = false;
594 for (hb_tag_t tag : pending_subset_tags)
595 {
596 if (!_dependencies_satisfied (plan, tag,
597 subsetted_tags,
598 pending_subset_tags))
599 {
600 // delayed subsetting for some tables since they might have dependency on other tables
601 // in some cases: e.g: during instantiating glyf tables, hmetrics/vmetrics are updated
602 // and saved in subset plan, hmtx/vmtx subsetting need to use these updated metrics values
603 continue;
604 }
605
606 pending_subset_tags.del (g: tag);
607 subsetted_tags.add (g: tag);
608 made_changes = true;
609
610 success = _subset_table (plan, buf, tag);
611 if (unlikely (!success)) goto end;
612 }
613
614 if (!made_changes)
615 {
616 DEBUG_MSG (SUBSET, nullptr, "Table dependencies unable to be satisfied. Subset failed.");
617 success = false;
618 goto end;
619 }
620 }
621
622 if (success && plan->attach_accelerator_data) {
623 _attach_accelerator_data (plan, face: plan->dest);
624 }
625
626end:
627 return success ? hb_face_reference (face: plan->dest) : nullptr;
628}

632#include "hb-ot-name-language-static.hh"
633#endif
